### Issue description

There is a bug in cocos/asset/asset-manager/editor-path-replace.ts. 
When the network is disconnected, the callback of bundle.load's loading completion will not be triggered. The fetchText method does not listen to the ontimeout, onerror, onabort and other exceptions during network requests, which results in the upper layer's then / catch not being able to execute.

`
 const fetchText = (url): Promise<unknown> => new Promise((resolve, reject): void => {
        const xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
        xhr.open('GET', url, true);
        xhr.onload = (): void => {
            if (xhr.status !== 200) {
                reject();
                return;
            }
            resolve(xhr.response);
        };
       
        /**  此处缺少对网络异常错误等情况的处理  需要  reject();  如 ontimeout, onerror, onabort   */
        xhr.onerror = ()=>{   reject();  };
        xhr.ontimeout = ()=>{   reject();  };
        xhr.onabort  = ()=>{   reject();  };
       /** */
       xhr.send(null);


    });`

